Constructor Detail

OrientorConfig

public OrientorConfig(java.lang.String url)
Creates a new OrientorConfig from the file at the specified URL. If the configuration file cannot be loaded (e.g., it does not exist), then the OrientorConfig is set up with a single dummy model named "Default", whose definition is obtained from the OrientorConfig.FallbackModel resource bundle.

Parameters:
url - the location of the configuration file to load.
Throws:
java.lang.RuntimeException - if there was an error requesting the file.

wireFrameLoaded

private void wireFrameLoaded()
Called when a wire-frame is loaded. Used to update wireFramesToLoad variable. Currently calls Config.doneLoading() when the countdown reaches zero and ensures there's a default wire-frame.
